                            <comment id="13105726" author="tlipcon" created="Thu, 15 Sep 2011 22:08:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;How does this relate to the servlet at /conf provided by Hadoop&apos;s HttpServer in recent versions?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13105728" author="nspiegelberg" created="Thu, 15 Sep 2011 22:18:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;@Todd : so Hadoop already has a similar webpage?  Also, one of the critical issues is adding &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HADOOP-7628&quot; title=&quot;Update the getProps() as a protected function in Configuration class for HBaseConfiguration &quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HADOOP-7628&quot;&gt;HADOOP-7628&lt;/a&gt; so we can also generate a list of the config values read and what their default is set to.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13105754" author="stack" created="Thu, 15 Sep 2011 23:07:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;@Nicolas It does.  HBase TRUNK picks up the hadoop facility showing all configs in hbase context.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13113614" author="liyin" created="Fri, 23 Sep 2011 18:00:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;@stack @Todd, what&apos;s the jira number for showing all configs in hbase context.&lt;br/&gt;
Thanks a lot&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13113762" author="stack" created="Fri, 23 Sep 2011 21:01:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;@Liyin I don&apos;t believe there is one.  It came for free when we moved to later hadoop.  We don&apos;t have it exposed in our UI IIRC.  We need to add a link along the top.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13114020" author="liyin" created="Sat, 24 Sep 2011 17:37:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;@stack. Which hadoop version I should rebase on for my patch. I have a pending patch but based on the hadoop-0.20-append.&lt;br/&gt;
Thanks&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13114026" author="liyin" created="Sat, 24 Sep 2011 17:56:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think the feature Todd mentioned is &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HADOOP-6408&quot; title=&quot;Add a /conf servlet to dump running configuration&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HADOOP-6408&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HADOOP-6408&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HADOOP-6408&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HADOOP-6408&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13114102" author="tlipcon" created="Sat, 24 Sep 2011 23:31:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes, that&apos;s the Hadoop feature I was referring to. If you run HBase with a Hadoop version that includes that patch, the /conf servlet does indeed function.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13117573" author="liyin" created="Thu, 29 Sep 2011 19:56:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;@stack,is it true that all the patches for hbase trunk should rebase on hadoop trunk or hadoop-0.24 (the latest release) ? &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13117874" author="liyin" created="Fri, 30 Sep 2011 04:34:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;@Todd, I have created a &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HADOOP-7702&quot; title=&quot;Show the default configuration value in /conf servlet as well&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HADOOP-7702&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HADOOP-7702&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, which will show all the default configuration value in /conf servlet.&lt;br/&gt;
So HBase can reuse them for fee. &lt;br/&gt;
Can you assign that jira to me? &lt;br/&gt;
Thanks &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13117875" author="liyin" created="Fri, 30 Sep 2011 04:34:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;@Todd, I have created a &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HADOOP-7702&quot; title=&quot;Show the default configuration value in /conf servlet as well&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HADOOP-7702&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HADOOP-7702&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, which will show all the default configuration value in /conf servlet.&lt;br/&gt;
So HBase can reuse them for fee. &lt;br/&gt;
Can you assign that jira to me? &lt;br/&gt;
Thanks &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13118514" author="stack" created="Fri, 30 Sep 2011 22:21:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;@Liyin We&apos;ll likely commit 0.20.205 to hbase when its released.  We&apos;ll put it in trunk and on 0.92 branch I&apos;d say.  It does not have the /conf stuff in it.  Maybe we should have hbase trunk include hadoop 0.23?  Have mvn depend on a 0.23-snapshot till its released?  I&apos;d assign you hadoop-7702 if I could figure out how to add contributors in the new jira interface....&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13118524" author="tlipcon" created="Fri, 30 Sep 2011 22:32:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;There&apos;s a bug in the new JIRA where we can&apos;t currently add contributors &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/sad.gif&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We can put the /conf servlet in 0.20.206, perhaps?&lt;br/&gt;
BTW, &quot;mvn -Dhadoop23&quot; will build against hadoop 23 (though currently broken)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13118542" author="liyin" created="Fri, 30 Sep 2011 22:54:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks stack and Todd.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I have attached a very simple patch here. If user runs hadoop with &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HADOOP-6408&quot; title=&quot;Add a /conf servlet to dump running configuration&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HADOOP-6408&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HADOOP-6408&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, /conf will show all the hbase configuration.&lt;br/&gt;
If user run hadoop without &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HADOOP-6408&quot; title=&quot;Add a /conf servlet to dump running configuration&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HADOOP-6408&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HADOOP-6408&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, nothing will change&lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.gif&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;What do you guys think?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13118544" author="liyin" created="Fri, 30 Sep 2011 22:54:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;BTW, I have tested it with hadoop-22 and it works.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13118579" author="liyin" created="Sat, 1 Oct 2011 00:00:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Add 2 links from Master and Region Server to configuration xml.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13118585" author="liyin" created="Sat, 1 Oct 2011 00:07:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;@stack, &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-4418&quot; title=&quot;Show all the hbase configuration in the web ui&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-4418&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-4418&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;_2.patch has 2 links from master and region server web ui to configuration page.&lt;br/&gt;
if you would make hbase-trunk based on hadoop-0.23, then &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-4418&quot; title=&quot;Show all the hbase configuration in the web ui&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-4418&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-4418&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;_2.patch is better.&lt;br/&gt;
Otherwise &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-4418&quot; title=&quot;Show all the hbase configuration in the web ui&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-4418&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-4418&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;_1.patch is better.&lt;br/&gt;
Thanks&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13118660" author="stack" created="Sat, 1 Oct 2011 04:11:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks Liyin.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13126979" author="liyin" created="Thu, 13 Oct 2011 21:46:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;@stack, it is pretty safte to commit &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-4418&quot; title=&quot;Show all the hbase configuration in the web ui&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-4418&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-4418&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;_1.patch &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.gif&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13130003" author="liyin" created="Tue, 18 Oct 2011 20:36:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Using refection to check whether the hadoop supports showing configuration in /conf servlet (&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HADOOP-6408&quot; title=&quot;Add a /conf servlet to dump running configuration&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HADOOP-6408&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HADOOP-6408&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;).&lt;br/&gt;
If the hadoop supports &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HADOOP-6408&quot; title=&quot;Add a /conf servlet to dump running configuration&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HADOOP-6408&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HADOOP-6408&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, the master and region server web ui will have the link to show HBase configuration.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13130014" author="nspiegelberg" created="Tue, 18 Oct 2011 20:49:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1. Thanks Liyin&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
